description.p:
The low-rate omni-directional mode should be used as minimally as possible. It is proposed to use it only for the minimal set of MAC/PHY functions which are required before switching to the directional mode and perform all other communications in the directional mode only. Such minimal set of PHY/MAC functions may include:



    

Low-rate omni-directional beacon;

Low-rate association request command;

Beamforming training frame;

Beamforming retraining request;

The duration for the Omni-CAP may be made variable and contain different number of time slots depending on the following factors:



    

Environment—the probability of the new DEVs entering the network may depend on the type of environment—e.g. residential or office environment;

Number of the associated DEVs—the probability of the event that some DEV will lose a beamformed connection with the PNC and will require sending a omni-directional beamforming retraining request frame will be higher for the large number of the associated DEVs;

claim.claim-text:
1. An apparatus, comprising:
one or more transceivers operable to communicate in a wireless network by using a low-rate omni directional mode and a high rate directional millimeter wave (mm wave) communications mode with beamformed antennas and a transmission is done using consecutive in time superframes divided into functional periods with the functional period intervals set by a piconet controller (PNC), wherein the wireless network is a wireless personal area network (WPAN) and wherein the WPAN is a piconet that includes a central station, and other station devices (DEVs);
wherein one superframe includes the following functional periods: Omni-Beacon Period, Omni-Contention Access Period (Omni-CAP), Directional Beacons Period, Announcement Period, Directional Channel Time Allocation Period (Directional CTAP) and Beamforming Period;
wherein when a request is received from a device for a Beamforming Period to perform beamforming training between different DEVs the piconet controller places the Beamforming Period after the Announcement Period or at the end of the superframe after the Directional CTAP;
wherein if the Beamforming Period is placed after the Announcement Period then a pair of devices are able to perform the beamforming training and to transmit during the Directional CTAP within the same superframe;
wherein if the beamforming period is placed after the Directional CTAP then the Beamforming Period is adjacent to the Omni-Beacon Period or after the Directional Beacon Period.

2. The apparatus of claim 1, wherein during the functional period a transceiver can transition between the low-rate omni directional mode and the high rate directional millimeter wave (mm wave) communications mode;
wherein if the Beamforming Period is adjacent to the Omni-Beacon Period then the transceiver transitions from the low-rate omni directional mode to the high rate directional millimeter wave (mm wave) communications mode only once during the superframe; and
wherein if the beamforming period is placed after the Directional Beacon Period then the there are two transitions from the low-rate omni directional mode to the high rate directional millimeter wave (mm wave) communications mode during the superframe.

6. A method, comprising:
communicating using one or more transceivers in a wireless network using a low-rate omni directional mode and a high rate directional millimeter wave (mm wave) communications mode and a transmission is done using consecutive in time superframes divided into functional periods with the functional period intervals set by a piconet controller (PNC), wherein the wireless network is a wireless personal area network (WPAN) and wherein the WPAN is a piconet that includes a central station and other station devices (DEVs);
using the low-rate omni-directional communications mode to send an omni directional beacon frame; and
using the low-rate omni-directional communications mode to send a message indicating a loss of a connection in the high rate directional communications mode;
wherein one superframe includes the following functional periods: Omni-Beacon Period, Omni-Contention Access Period (Omni-CAP), Directional Beacons Period, Announcement Period, Directional Channel Time Allocation Period (Directional CTAP) and Beamforming Period;
wherein when a request is received from a device for a Beamforming Period to perform beamforming training between different DEVs the piconet controller places the Beamforming Period after the Announcement Period or at the end of the superframe after the Directional CTAP;
wherein if the Beamforming Period is placed after the Announcement Period then a pair of devices are able to perform the beamforming training and to transmit during the Directional CTAP within the same superframe;
wherein if the beamforming period is placed after the Directional CTAP then the Beamforming Period is adjacent to the Omni-Beacon Period or after the Directional Beacon Period.

7. The method of claim 6, wherein during the functional period a transceiver can transition between the low-rate omni directional mode and the high rate directional millimeter wave (mm wave) communications mode;
wherein if the Beamforming Period is adjacent to the Omni-Beacon Period then the transceiver transitions from the low-rate omni directional mode to the high rate directional millimeter wave (mm wave) communications mode only once during the superframe; and
wherein if the beamforming period is placed after the Directional Beacon Period then the there are two transitions from the low-rate omni directional mode to the high rate directional millimeter wave (mm wave) communications mode during the superframe.

11. A non-transitory machine-accessible medium that provides instructions, which when accessed, cause a machine to perform operations comprising:
communicating in a wireless network using a low-rate omni directional mode and a high rate directional millimeter wave (mm wave) communications mode and a transmission is done using consecutive in time superframes divided into functional periods with the functional period intervals set by a piconet controller (PNC), wherein the wireless network is a wireless personal area network (WPAN) and wherein the WPAN is a piconet that includes a central station and other station devices (DEVs);
using the low-rate omni-directional communications mode to send an omni directional beacon frame; and
using the low-rate omni-directional communications mode to send a message indicating a loss of a connection in the high rate directional communications mode;
wherein one superframe includes the following functional periods: Omni-Beacon Period, Omni-Contention Access Period (Omni-CAP), Directional Beacons Period, Announcement Period, Directional Channel Time Allocation Period (Directional CTAP) and Beamforming Period;
wherein when a request is received from a device for a Beamforming Period to perform beamforming training between different DEVs the piconet controller places the Beamforming Period after the Announcement Period or at the end of the superframe after the Directional CTAP;
wherein if the Beamforming Period is placed after the Announcement Period then a pair of devices are able to perform the beamforming training and to transmit during the Directional CTAP within the same superframe;
wherein if the beamforming period is placed after the Directional CTAP then the Beamforming Period is adjacent to the Omni-Beacon Period or after the Directional Beacon Period.
